-- Real Madrid Wants Arsenal's Gael Clichy for Karim Benzema: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2010-12-16T11:56:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-16/real-madrid-wants-arsenal-s-gael-clichy-for-karim-benzema-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Real Wants Clichy  Real Madrid will offer striker  Karim Benzema  to Arsenal in
exchange for defender  Gael Clichy , the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The Spanish club, which signed Benzema for $50 million, is
ready to cut its losses as it plans “transfer action” in the
January window, the Mirror said.  Grant Ultimatum  Sam Allardyce  could become West Ham coach if  Avram Grant 
fails to lead the Hammers to at least one win in its next three
games, the  Daily Mail  reported.  The team owners are eager to speak to Allardyce after he
was dismissed by Blackburn, the Mail said. West Ham’s next games
are against Blackburn, Fulham and Everton.  Shearer’s Return?  Alan Shearer  is interested in returning to Blackburn to
become coach, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  Shearer, who helped the team become champion in 1995,
failed to prevent Newcastle from being relegated in a brief
tenure as coach in 2009.  Al Fayed Pledge  Fulham owner Mohamed Al Fayed has told Mark Hughes his job
as coach is safe and promised 10 million pounds ($15.6 million)
to spend on players, the  Daily Mail  reported.  Hughes is interested in acquiring Manchester City’s  Roque Santa Cruz , according to the Mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
